args: Ahhh, this is PERFECT sunbathing weather!
Mommy, look! I caught a big bug!
Wow, that's amazing! It looks a little sad\nthough, so maybe you should let it go.
Mommy, look! I caught a big fiend!
You truly ARE our daughter. It looks a little\nsad though, so maybe you should let it go.
Goo goo gah gah! WAAAH! WAAAH!
My goodness, somebody got up on\nthe wrong side of the crib today!
Well, maybe this will make it better...\nPeek-a-dragon!
I tell you, honey, being surrounded\nby our darling children is what true\nhappiness is all about.
Thank every single one of you for being\nborn and coming into our lives!
Augh! I can't let that dream stay a dream!\nI MUST make it a reality!
Hmm... But can a dragon and a human\neven MAKE babies?
Ah! I'll go ask Midgardsormr and Mercury!\nThey'll surely know something.
Grrrrr! That Mercury is SUCH a cad!
＂Though you may assume a similar guise,\nhumans and dragons are completely\ndifferent and can never produce children.＂
What nerve! What utter cheek!\nSurely the power of love will find a way!

＂The difference in your lifespans is great,
so even if you remained married for life,
he would grow old and decay, leaving you
feeling naught but heartache.＂
I mean, come on! There must be some...
I heard from the other dragons that there\nwas something strange going on with you,\nand it had me somewhat worried.
I used to think that humans were\nterrifically boring creatures.
They are weak, and their lives short.\nI thanked my lucky stars every day\nthat I was born a dragon.
If I were a human, you and I could bear\nchildren, grow old, and pass on together.
Is that what's been bothering you?
Why was I born a dragon...?
Listen, Mym. I've got something\nI'd like to ask of you.
Something only you, a dragon, can do.
In all likelihood, I'm going to leave\nthis world long before you.
When that happens, will you watch over\nand protect it in my stead?
You want me to carry on your dream?
Yes. We both love this world, after all,\nand I can think of no one better.
We got trouble, guys!\nFiends are attacking a village!
Just think about it, all right, Mym?\nIt's not like we don't have plenty to\ndo in the meantime anyway.
This world that we both love...
This world is proof of our love.\nIt IS our child!
Heh. It can be a real handful at times,\nbut it's still our adorable little child.
Thank you, darling. I feel much better now.
Now I will give my all—for my love\nof both my darling AND this world!
